    skos:notation "4.2.6" ;
    dcterms:identifier "426" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Spruce, pine and larch mire forests"@en ;
    skos:definition "Forests (>30% canopy cover) dominated by spruce (Picea abies or P. obovata) on acid peat or around active bogs and poor fens with nutrient-poor ground waters occurring through the boreal zone and locally, where ground conditions permit, in the continental zone; Open forests (with lower canopy cover) dominated by pine (Pinus mugo subsp. rotundata, Pinus sylvestris) or larch (Larix decidua, L. sibirica) on acid peat or around active bogs and poor fens with nutrient-poor ground waters occurring through the boreal zone and locally, where ground conditions permit, in the continental zone. Includes burnt areas of this type."@en ;
    skos:broader <https://w3id.org/italia/env/vocab/ecosystems/typologies/4.2> ;
