    skos:notation "4.2.7" ;
    dcterms:identifier "427" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Taiga forests"@en ;
    skos:definition "Taiga forests: found in the boreal zone of North-Eastern Europe and western Siberia including deciduous taiga dominated by Siberian larch (Larix sibirica) and evergreen taiga dominated by Pinus sylvestris, with spruce (Picea abies and Picea obovata), Siberian fir (Abies sibirica), Siberian pine (Pinus sibirica), Betula pendula and Betula pubescens). Includes burnt areas of this type."@en ;
    skos:broader <https://w3id.org/italia/env/vocab/ecosystems/typologies/4.2> ;
